releases.name: v0.3.0-beta.3
releases.body:
- Fixes a bug in the `bulk_load_dataset` method that was creating an invalid database.
- Server: Takes into account also URL query parameters if the send SPARQL request body is using form-urlencoded.
- Some release artefacts improvements.

releases.name: v0.3.0-beta.2
releases.body: Fixes release on crates.io of the RocksDB bindings.

releases.name: v0.3.0-beta.1
releases.body:
First beta of the 0.3 release. A lot of major changes.

* [RocksDB](http://rocksdb.org/) is now the only supported storage backend. This storage is named `Store` in the Rust, Python and JS APIs. The other storage systems are not available anymore.
* [RDF-star](https://w3c.github.io/rdf-star/cg-spec) is now implemented.
* All operations are now transactional using the "repeatable read" isolation level: the store only exposes changes that have been "committed" (i.e. no partial writes) and the exposed state does not change for the complete duration of a read operation (e.g. a SPARQL query) or a read/write operation (e.g. a SPARQL update).

Read [the CHANGELOG](https://github.com/oxigraph/oxigraph/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md) for a more detailed description of the changes.

releases.name: v0.2.5
releases.body: Adds JSON SPARQL results parser and releases Cargo.lock to fix build after bad dependency changes.

releases.name: v0.2.4
releases.body: Allows to query the union graph from the HTTP server and adds methods to flush Sled store.

releases.name: v0.2.3
releases.body: Fixes HTTP content negotiation in Oxigraph server

releases.name: v0.2.2
releases.body:
Various bug fix:
- Allows unsupported query parameters in HTTP SPARQL requests
- Adds support of XML entities to the RDF/XML parser
- Fixes named graph creation inside of a SledStore transaction

releases.name: v0.2.1
releases.body: Fixes pyoxigraph build after a new release of the build tool `maturin`

releases.name: v0.2.0
releases.body:
Second main release of Oxigraph.

The highlights of this release are:
- [SPARQL 1.1 Update](https://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-update/) support.
- [SPARQL 1.1 Graph Store HTTP Protocol](https://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-http-rdf-update/) partial support in `oxigraph_server`.
- The SPARQL algebra is now public allowing tool analysing SPARQL queries to be built on top of Oxigraph.
- The stores can now contain empty named graphs.

The disk data format has been changed between Oxigraph 0.1 (version 0) and Oxigraph 0.2 (version 1). Data is automatically migrated from the version 0 format to the version 1 format when opened with Oxigraph 0.2.

releases.name: v0.1.1
releases.body:
Bug fix and small features release:

- Adds the "sophia" feature implementing the sophia_api traits on Oxigraph terms and stores.
- Adds explicit types for quads iterators returned by stores.
- `QueryOptions::with_default_graph` now takes an `impl Into<GraphName>` instead of an `impl Into<NamedNode>`.
- `QueryOptions::with_named_graph` now takes an `impl Into<NamedOrBlankNode>` instead of an `impl Into<NamedNode>`.
- `pyoxigraph` `query` methods now takes two new parameters, `default_graph` and `named_graphs`. `default_graph_uris` and `named_graph_uris` parameters are deprecated.
- Fixes a bug in `xsd:gYear` parsing.
